The `collect_into_vec(&mut directory_tests_results)` + pre-declared `Vec` pattern is unnecessary here. You can simplify this to:

```rust
let directory_tests_results: Vec<_> = dir_entries
    .into_par_iter()
    .map(|entry| -> Result<Option<Vec<Test>>, RunnerError> {
        // ... same closure body ...
    })
    .collect();
```

This is what the v1 runner does at `state/parser.rs:71-76` for its top-level collection, and it removes the need for the `IndexedParallelIterator` import.
